Scarlett Johansson is sitting in a simple white room. She's looking down the camera directly at us.  She’s talking about when she first discovered that there was a deepfake porn video of her on the internet.

"I actually wasn't surprised.  The internet is a vast wormhole of darkness that eats itself but I was afraid.  Not for myself but for vulnerable people who don’t have a platform to defend themselves.  There’s nothing to stop someone from cutting and pasting my image or your image onto a different body and making it look as realistic as desired.  It just depends on whether or not someone has the desire to target you and that to me is terrifying..."

We zoom out from the image of Scarlett's face and reveal a split screen. Scarlett is on the right hand side, on the left is another woman - we see that the facial expressions of the woman on the left are being used to manipulate Scarlett’s face.  When this woman smiles Scarlett smiles, when this woman talks, Scarlett says her words.  

We haven’t been watching an interview with Scarlett Johansson at all but a live deepfake in which Scarlett is being used as a puppet.

As this awareness begins to sink in we cut to another familiar face. It's Obama.  He's dressed in a suit, sitting in a mahogany chair looking directly at the camera and addressing the American people, behind him hangs a U.S. flag:

"We're entering an era in which our enemies can make it look like anyone is saying anything at any point in time - even if they would never say those things. So, for instance, they could have me say things like, I don't know... President Trump is a total dipshit."
"This is a dangerous time. Moving forward, we need to be more vigilant with what we trust from the internet,"

One after another, some of the most recognizable faces of our time begin to fill the screen. We see Putin, then Trump, Oprah, Hillary Clinton, Arnold Schwarzenegger and Beyonce. The faces are familiar but this time the voices do not match. The faces shapeshift and merge.

DEEPFAKES is a mind-bending four-part series set inside the lives of the unforgettable characters who are creating the future and disrupting the present. Inhabiting every corner of our real and virtual world, they are leather-wearing, motorbike-riding AI pioneers and mysterious Russians on Reddit, Hollywood executives and renegade coders. There’s the investigative journalist in India, deepfaked into porn by her political enemies, whose life is under threat, and famous faces including Scarlett Johansson and Jim Carrey, who have found themselves suddenly at the center of the deepfake storm. And, in the deep recesses of 8CHAN, there are the dark beginnings of coordinated efforts to undermine the 2020 election.

Weaving between the Hollywood Hills, Washington, D.C., Beijing and Eastern Europe, from the darkest recesses of the internet and the halls of Congress, this propulsive four-part thriller is a wild ride through uncharted territory that will leave viewers questioning everything.

Over four episodes, the series will, for the first time, tell the surprising story of where deepfakes came from, from the earliest days of computer graphics to the present-day explosion of proprietary techniques and easily accessible iPhone apps alike, always exploring both the incredible possibilities and deep consequences of the technology for all of us. We will follow in real time, from the inside, how the stuff of Hollywood is excitingly created, and then how it is being weaponized to undermine our faith in our leaders and democracy itself. And we will break the fourth wall, working with the technology's savants to create and release our own narrative trojan horse - a provocative deepfake that we will track during the course of production as it goes from idea to execution to viral sensation.

In addition, we will work with provocateur and creator of the famous Bill Hader and Jim Carrey deepfakes CTRL SHIFT FACE to create an entirely original deepfake and release it into the world, tracking the process and impact over all four episodes of the series.
The experience of watching the series will match the wildness of the topic itself, inspiring awe, thrills, dread, and laughs in equal measure, every answer leading to another big question.

The series will use all the tricks of the trade to play with the viewer's sense of reality - key sections will be deepfakes of our own creation that toy with the viewer's sense of what's true and what's not. In an unprecedented subversion of the documentary genre, seeing won't quite be believing as our key characters shapeshift and meld into one another.  We’ll 'interview' Scarlett Johansson and President Obama leaving the audience to wonder - is it really them? A unique audio-visual experience, this series will be disorienting, mind-bending and life-altering, changing how we see the 'real' world forever.

Ari Handel received a PhD in Neuroscience then left academia to become President of Protozoa Pictures, with whom he’s worked as a writer and/or producer on The Fountain, The Wrestler, Black Swan, Noah, Jackie, mother!, SPHERES, and most recently National Geographic’s One Strange Rock.  Handel is co-chairman of the board of The Moth, the Peabody and Macarthur Award winning not-for-profit dedicated to the art and craft of storytelling.

Two Time Academy Award®-Nominee, two-time Emmy Winner, Peabody Winner, Grammy Nominee, and DGA-Nominated director, Liz Garbus is one of the most celebrated documentary filmmakers working today. Garbus’ latest docuseries The Fourth Estate, for Showtime, was nominated for a 2018 Emmy for Outstanding Documentary or Nonfiction Series. What Happened, Miss Sim-one?, a Netflix original, was nominated for a 2016 Oscar for Best Documentary Feature and took home the Emmy Award for Best Documentary or Nonfiction Special. Currently, Garbus is in post-production on Lost Girls, a scripted feature for Netflix based on the book by the same name, starring Amy Ryan, Gabriel Byrne, and Thomasin McKenzie.

Darren Aronofsky is the Academy Award®-nominated filmmaker behind mother!, Noah, Black Swan, The Wrestler, The Fountain, Requiem for a Dream and π.  As a producer, he worked on the films Jackie, White Boy Rick, and Pacified, which recently took home The Golden Shell at the San Sebastian Film Festival. He is executive producer of One Strange Rock for NatGeo, which has been viewed over 100 million times, and of the virtual reality series SPHERES: Songs of Spacetime, winner of the Grand Prix in VR at the 2018 Venice Film Festival. Aronofsky is an ardent advocate of science and the environment and a board member of the Sierra Club Foundation and the School for Field Studies.

Dan Cogan is the Academy Award®-winning producer of Icarus and the Executive Director and Co-Founder of Impact Partners, a fund and advisory service for investors and philanthropists who seek to promote social change through film.  Since its inception in 2007, Impact Partners has financed over 100 films, including Won’t You Be My Neighbor?, which won the 2019 Independent Spirit Award for Best Documentary, and THE COVE, which won the 2010 Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature.
